- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes a new clustering method that can be applied to large networks, which is relevant to software engineering.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for clustering networks.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses edge centralities to map vertices onto points of a Euclidean space, which is a common technique in machine learning.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the problem of scalability in clustering networks, which is relevant to systems and control.
